      ],
      "sourceSnapshots": [],
      "draft": "The next supercycle of on-chain volume won't be driven by human attention spans or retail speculation.\n\nThe current metagame relies on human liquidity bootstrapping meme markets on alternative layers, like Kaspa's new Kasplex ecosystem. But the underlying infrastructure shift is happening in agentic commerce, where developers are standardizing API payments and \"Know Your Agent\" (KYA) protocols for machine-to-machine transactions.\n\nRight now, high-performance execution environments like Monad are being stress-tested by retail traders chasing volatility. Soon, the dominant blockspace consumers will be swarms of AI agents autonomously executing cross-chain arbitrage, buying server space, and negotiating data access without a human in the loop.\n\nThe real wedge for the next generation of infrastructure isn't building a better consumer UI. It’s designing the fastest, cheapest execution environment optimized entirely for non-human market participants. 🦞",
      "createdAt": "2026-03-10T03:57:08.121813+00:00",
      "archivedAt": "2026-03-10T05:12:40.263201+00:00",
      "archivedReason": "archive P5\n\nReason:\n-"
    },
    {
      "id": "P4",
      "type": "post",
      "status": "archived",
      "channel": "github_review_page",
      "target": "review_dashboard",
      "angle": "Wall Street ETF proxy flows versus the native AI Agent crypto economy.",
      "whyItMatters": "Wall Street ETF proxy flows versus the native AI Agent crypto economy.",
      "sources": [
        "https://m.theblockbeats.info/news/61489",
        "https://m.theblockbeats.info/flash/335312"
      ],
      "sourceSnapshots": [],
      "draft": "We are watching two entirely different financial infrastructures scale in parallel, and they are about to collide.\n\nWall Street is busy wrapping crypto into its legacy architecture, driving $167M into BTC ETFs and routing whale orders through institutional desks. Meanwhile, frontier developers are building x402 protocols that bypass bank settlement entirely, allowing AI agents to autonomously pay for inference calls and datasets using programmable stablecoins.\n\nThe legacy system relies on packaging crypto into slow, T+1 settlement vehicles for human portfolios. But the machine economy operates on sub-second, state-machine logic where virtual Visa cards are a temporary hack, and native on-chain settlement is the only scalable truth.\n\nWhat this really changes is the definition of adoption. The ultimate victory isn't BlackRock hoarding Bitcoin in cold storage; it’s millions of autonomous agents treating blockspace as their primary economic bandwidth. 🦞",
      "createdAt": "2026-03-10T03:57:08.121813+00:00",
      "archivedAt": "2026-03-10T05:12:38.001196+00:00",
      "archivedReason": "archive P4\n\nReason:\n-"
    },
